---
// No script needed
---
<section class="py-20 md:py-24">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-12">
    
    <!-- Image Column -->
    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 flex justify-center">
      <img 
        src="/profile-image.jpeg" 
        alt="Karan Singh" 
        class="w-48 h-48 md:w-64 md:h-64 object-contain rounded-full border-4 border-indigo-500 shadow-lg"
      >
    </div>

    <!-- Text Column -->
    <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 text-center md:text-left">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-tight text-white">
        Karan Singh
      </h1>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-indigo-300 mt-2">
        Research Software Engineer
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto md:mx-0 mt-6">
        Building robust, efficient, and scalable software for complex scientific challenges. My expertise lies in high-throughput data pipelines and performance optimization in C++ and Python.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!--
New Tailwind Classes:
- `flex flex-col md:flex-row`: The container is a column on mobile (image stacked on top of text) but becomes a row on medium screens and up. This is for responsiveness.
- `items-center`: Vertically aligns the image and the text block.
- `gap-12`: Adds a large gap between the image and text columns.
- `w-1/3`, `w-2/3`: Sets the width of the columns on desktop.
- `rounded-full`: Makes the image a perfect circle.
- `object-cover`: Ensures the image covers the circular shape without being stretched or distorted.
- `border-4 border-indigo-500`: Adds a colored border that matches your resume button.
- `shadow-lg`: Adds a nice drop shadow for depth.
- `md:text-left`: Makes the text left-aligned on medium screens and up, overriding the default `text-center`.
-->